{"name":"Accelerate Healing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The power accelerates the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} &nbsp;rate. With a successful casting the target may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} roll every six hours for a 24 hour period, with a +2 bonus if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. With a success, the target also gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls for resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease} during the same time, and a +4 bonus with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The target may only be affected by one casting of accelerate healing at a time.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"y9oZyY6DdHfEyn6h"}
{"name":"Analyze Foe","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Knowledge is power. Being able to judge the strength of a foe before engaging him in combat can be highly advantageous.</p>\n<p>The character makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. On a success, he gains a +1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the target, and the target suffers a &ndash;1 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the caster. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the effect is increased to +2 and &ndash;2 for both.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Information (+2): </strong>For 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, a success allows the caster to learn of a single @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Immunity]{Immunity}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Invulnerability]{Invulnerability}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weakness} of the target (if one exists), and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} allows the knowledge of two.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ogxStX93TaeTrKr0"}
{"name":"Animate War Tree","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>War trees are semi-sentient, animated trees, created usually only in desperate times of need.</p>\n<p>With a success, the hero awakens one tree (which must be taller than 30') he is touching as a war tree. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the animated tree is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UPkTmrG7LgZpgshX]{Wild Card}. At the end of the spell's duration, the war tree transforms back into a regular tree. If the war tree is killed before this time, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Tree becomes covered in runes, warps into a \"tree man.\"","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"S5RUjt96mixQYoDO"}
{"name":"Augury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>By casting gem-inlaid sticks, rolling dragon bones, laying out ornate cards, or employing some other divining tool, you receive an omen from an otherworldly entity about the results of a specific course of action that you plan to take within the next 30 minutes, The DM chooses from the following possible omens:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Weal</em>, for good results</li>\n<li><em>Woe</em>, for bad results</li>\n<li><em>Weal and woe</em>, for both good and bad results</li>\n<li><em>Nothing</em>, for results that aren't especially good or bad</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The spell doesn't take into account any possible circumstances that might change the outcome, such as the casting of additional spells or the loss or gain of a companion.</p>\n<p>If you cast the spell two or more times before 24 hours pass, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get a random reading. The DM makes this roll in secret.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"1 minute","trapping":"Reading of cards, casting of bones.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Epxpd6EJsCJzVQKh"}
{"name":"Battle Song","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This spell, beloved of warlike bards, skalds and dirgesingers, causes the targets to fly into a battle frenzy.</p>\n<p>Every creature within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VQvyYBQG9Gh4VdWa]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster, apart from the caster, is granted the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.d0YwZF1Sf0cJgxJ4]{Berserk} Edge for the duration of the spell. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the targets immediately go berserk, as per the Edge. Unwilling recipients are allowed a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} &nbsp;to resist. This spell affects friends and foe alike.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>For 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power effects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VQvyYBQG9Gh4VdWa]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"5","trapping":"Poetry, battle chant.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"D8mStqfkzcaKyVDz"}
{"name":"Becalm","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Becalm</em> affects a single sailed-ship of any size, halving its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.mRtj0ALqtfNzugbo]{Top Speed}&nbsp;for the duration. A ship may be affected by multiple castings of this spell, though neither @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.mRtj0ALqtfNzugbo]{Top Speed} nor @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.mRtj0ALqtfNzugbo]{Acceleration}&nbsp;may ever be reduced below 1. It has no effect on oared vessels.</p>\n<p><em>Becalm </em>also adds +2 to a ship's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.6U7wHNpFEuUSqLAs]{Boating} totals in a storm, whether magical or natural.</p>\n<p>The caster suffers a penalty to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{arcane skill} roll equal to one-quarter of the ship's base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.mRtj0ALqtfNzugbo]{Toughness} (ignore Armor), rounded down.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1): </strong>For each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Point} &nbsp;spent can offset one penalty point for the size of the ship.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Sight","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Caster stands on deck and sucks in air, arcane gestures, runes.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CABqZUrUy81OEM5F"}
{"name":"Bind Entity","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Bind entity</em> allows its user to force an entity into servitude. Any entity that can be summoned can generally be bound. The creature may be summoned and then bound, or it might already be in the physical world.</p>\n<p>The cost to invoke this spell is equal to twice the entity's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} die type. A demon with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} die of d8, for example, requires 16 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points} to cast bind entity on it.</p>\n<p>In either case, the caster makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} &nbsp;by the entity's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit}. If the entity is already subject to a <em>bind entity</em> spell it receives a +4 bonus to its roll.</p>\n<p>On a success, the caster has bound the creature to his will for the duration of the spell. The creature must obey commands given to it, both to the letter and spirit, though orders that would undeniably end the entity's existence allow it another roll to break free.</p>\n<p>There is no inherent mental link between the caster and the entity, so commands must be expressed by some method the creature understands.</p>\n<p>The caster may not try to bind the same entity more than once in any 24 hour period, nor may he attempt to bind the same entity for 24 hours after the current binding expires (though he may maintain the spell). The entity does not need to be in Range or even seen to maintain the power.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Chanting, wardings, special substances.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Meqi0I2hl7qbHNfH"}
{"name":"Champion of Faith","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This spell grants the cleric divine favor. For the duration of the spell, the caster gains the benefits of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.2mIJ6vED38b724e0]{Champion} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.x4LXFB8zi9JNiJn4]{Holy/Unholy Warrior} Edge, chosen at the time of casting. Both edges can be taken on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Casters with neither Edge may pick either one, regardless of whether they are a priest or paladin.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Holy Aura","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vX00noAgcyKXVsFR"}
{"name":"Consecrate Ground","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Consecrated ground</em> is anathema to creatures counter to the god or gods being invoked. Through the use of this power, an area of holy ground is created, filling a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.VQvyYBQG9Gh4VdWa]{Large Blast Template} centered on the caster.</p>\n<p>Any supernatural creatures counter to the gods invoked entering the area must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll or suffer a -2 penalty to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Trait} rolls while within the effects of the spell. The penalty is -4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the casting roll.</p>\n<p>Permanently consecrating an area, like a church or templte, is possible, but not usually within the confines of an adventure. High ranking priests, valuable oils and ungents, and saintly or other holy relics may be required, as is some sort of alter or other focus of worship.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1): </strong>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit}&nbsp;roll to resist the effect is made at -2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Large Burst Template","duration":"1 minute","trapping":"Circle fo holy water or salt, energy barrier, pentagram.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Vj3UvwlzhIuCmRrY"}
{"name":"Create Food and Drink","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The character creates enough food and water for three humanoids or one mount for 24 hours. The food and water appear on the ground or in containers within range. The food is bland but nourishing, and spoils if uneaten after 24 hours. The water is clean and doesn't go bad.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):&nbsp;</strong>The power creates food and water for three additional humanoids or one mount may be created for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points}.</li>\n<li><strong>Feast (+10): </strong>For an additional 10 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points}&nbsp;the food is not bland but the quality of a multi-course feast meal. Rather than water, any kind of drink of the hero's choice is created.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"24 hour","trapping":"Animating cooking utensils, waving hands over a table.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OOrRMTl3ETtjxV2x"}
{"name":"Creation","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Creation </em>allows the hero to create a non-magical, unattended object of nonliving vegatable matter. The volume of the object created cannot exceed 1 cubic foot per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{rank}. It can't rely on intricate artistry or complex moving parts, never fulfills a cost or the like, and can't be made of precious materials or materials with a rarity of uncommon or higher.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Complexity (+5): </strong>For 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{Power Points}, the hero can create an item that has modest artistry and modestly complex moving parts.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"1 hour","trapping":"Hands waving, animating a set of tools.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QJca0fngz85PI6Mg"}
{"name":"Curse","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Some practitioners of the arcane arts heal their allies; others inflict sickness upon their enemies. To use this particularly nasty spell, the caster makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the victim's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll. Failure means the victim suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{Fatigue} immediately. Each day at sunset the victim must make another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ZUQ9fsJ5ybqBIByu]{arcane skill} or suffer another level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{Fatigue} (further castings of curse have no additional effect).</p>\n<p>Once the accursed becomes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5Qbb2JuTeN4XHgH5]{Incapacitated}, he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{Vigor} roll each day to avoid death.</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking the Curse: </strong>The <em>curse</em> can be lifted by the original caster at will, and ends automatically if she's slain. <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.qTiLD4ZYauv51FHi]{Dispel}</em> also removes a curse, though each individual may only try once&mdash;if failed it's beyond her abilities.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","trapping":"Voodoo doll, burning incense, vile curse spoken","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iQR6hOsaiXq1690i"}
{"name":"Detect/Conceal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This spell replaces&nbsp;<em>detect/conceal arcana</em>. It uses the same basic game mechanics, except, when selecting the power the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Eyu98J7dnZCTrXrL]{trapping} must include what is able to be detected/concealed; arcana, poison, objects, traps, creatures, etc. When detecting, the character must name the type of object he seeks when casting. He can be vague (arcane, traps, secret doors, or gold) or specific (Baron Gustbran or an orc chieftain).&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Detect arcana</em> allows the recipient of the power to see and detect all supernatural persons, objects, or effects in sight for five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{rounds}. This includes <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Invisibilty]{invisible} </em>foes, enchantments on people or items, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Weird Science)]{weird science} devices, and so on. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the caster knows the general type of enchantment as well &mdash; harmful, obscurement, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Magic)]{magic}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{miracles}, etc.</p>\n<p><em>Detect arcana</em> also allows a character to ignore up to 4 points of penalties when attacking foes hidden by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Light / Darkness]{magical darkness}, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Invisibilty]{invisibilty}</em>, or similar abilities (or all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</p>\n<p><em>Conceal arcana </em>prevents detection of arcane energies on one being or item of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Normal Scale} for one hour.</p>\n<p><strong>Detect vs. Conceal</strong>: <em>Detecting arcana</em> against someone or something that&rsquo;s been <em>concealed </em>is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skills} (roll each time it&rsquo;s attempted, but no more than once per turn). If the <em>concealment </em>wins, the character cannot see through the ruse with this casting, but may terminate this instance and try again.</p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one viewer for <em>detect</em>, or item for&nbsp;<em>conceal,&nbsp;</em>for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1/+2):</strong> <em>Conceal&nbsp;</em>only. The power effects everything in a sphere the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} for +1 points, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +2</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Conceal </em>only. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Detection rolls} to see through the concealment are made at -2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"5 (detect), one hour (conceal)","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WwDL1x1EcJzArJEH"}
{"name":"Dimensional Leap","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>This is a renaming of the Teleport Power.</em></p>\n<p><em>Dimensional leap </em>allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to 12\"; (24 yards) distant, or double that with a raise. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a -2 penalty on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don't get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.YneMFEbKXaTaUZGb]{free attack} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.SKOCsEd2ECoe2R92]{Withdrawing from Melee} ).</p>\n<p>If casting <em>dimensional leap </em>on a willing subject, the caster decides where they move to, not the target.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Distance (+2): </strong>The caster may double the distance traveled.</li>\n<li><strong>Move Foe (+2): </strong>Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.7vhAtJWPrNgQ2V0p]{Touch attack}. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}, so the casting must be the second part of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.On57BX9RxFSOBjzj]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12\" away with success and 24\" with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, \"phasing\" out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Oi3TyW2uAYFyf2kW"}
{"name":"Dimensional Space","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Dimensional space</em> allows the hero to create an extradimensional space that is the space of four 10 foot cubes, that can hold up to eight creatures. The entrance to the space can be any kind of portal chosen in the trapping.</p>\n<p>Attacks and spells cannot cross through the entrance into or out of the extradimensional space. If the occupants of the space can see out into the outside world, then the outside world can also see into the dimensional space.</p>\n<p>The space does not include anything, but if anything is left when the spell ends, the items drop out of the <em>dimensional space</em>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):&nbsp;</strong>The space my hold an additional two creatures for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Size (+1): </strong>The power may double the size of the space for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} for every set of four 10 foot cubes.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Time (+5/+10): </strong>The space may last up to either hours for 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, or up to 24 hours for 10 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</li>\n<li><strong>Food and Drink (+3): </strong>The space can be furnished with enough food and drink for each occupant with a basic but nutritious meal for 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</li>\n<li><strong>Magnificent Mansion (+10): </strong>The power may add food and water to feed all the occupants of the space with a lavish meal. It will include one near-transparent servant for each occupant in the space. The space can be divided up into various lavishly appointed chambers to the desire of the hero.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour","trapping":"A rope climbed into a hidden space in the sky, door appears free standing, mystical portal.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Lv0HYKxbL2nArp92"}
{"name":"Elemental Form","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Powerful elementalists have a strong link to the elemental realms, and can convert their own body into elemental matter, if only for a short while.</p>\n<p>For the duration of the spell, the caster gains the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.KwAm2qYSl1LELKht]{Special Ability (Elemental)} of the appropriate elemental type. He retains his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{traits}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ubpz4RPjaPRSBNx0]{Hindrances}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.5r7x1AgEwLUihtZm]{Edges}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UmewRLXJsddUxY5X]{Size}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"1 minute","trapping":"Bit of element to be changed into, tattoos.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3UE0av9Rk7mjDipL"}
{"name":"False Health","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>While this spell does not actually heal, it does allow a character to disregard pain and its symptoms temporarily. With success, the target ignores up to 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} and 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.uQyy7EfJkaHAwXMp]{Fatigue} penalties, or 4/2 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Illusion, mesmerism, ointments, pain reduction.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OrTSSs0F1Qb861Sn"}
{"name":"Gift of Battle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Gift of battle </em>grants the target tactical insight and leadership qualities.</p>\n<p>Success allows the recipient to pick one Leadership Edge. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} means he can take two Edges. He need not meet any requirements except those of other Edges. For instance, the hero cannot gain @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.UKNT4ZWfFCYHbD6V]{Fervor} unless he scores a raise and takes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.jl9QT69V3DzHS2bq]{Command} first, or already has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.jl9QT69V3DzHS2bq]{Command} Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Battle cry, rallying speech, tactical insight.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VQ8MdqquzDpHc3nW"}
{"name":"Glyph","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>A <em>glyph </em>spell is a way of storing a single spell for activation under a predetermined trigger. <em>Glyphs </em>must be cast simultaneously with a single spell the caster knows.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Glyphs </em>remain magically charged until activated, which requires a specific trigger. A trigger must contain no more than 10 words, and no more than two clauses. <em>Glyphs </em>aren't intelligent, and although they can recognize their caster they cannot distinguish between other individuals or races. Example triggers are, \"Activate when anyone but me opens that door,\" \"Activate when touched by anyone but me,\" \"Activate when I cry 'Help,'\" and so on.</p>\n<p>A hero may have a maximum number of <em>glyphs </em>cast at anyone time equal to half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die. They never count as Maintained spells.</p>\n<p>Once triggered, the spell stored in the <em>glyph </em>goes off as normal. It uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.9IwLt34etK096UAK]{traits} of the caster at the time of the glyph's creation. Once activated, the <em>glyph </em>loses its magic. Maintained spells last for one hour once activated. The caster of a <em>glyph</em>, assuming he is alive, always knows when a <em>glyph </em>has been triggered, regardless of distance, though not which specific <em>glyph</em>.</p>\n<p><em>Glyphs </em>can be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.qTiLD4ZYauv51FHi]{dispelled}, but they cannot be disarmed by mundane means. The caster may erase a <em>glyph </em>he has created simply by touching it and dissolving the magic (an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}). He may also temporarily negate a <em>glyph</em>, thus allowing comrades to pass in safety but not those following him. Negating and reactivating a <em>glyph </em>in this manner takes an action each and requires the <em>glyph </em>to be touched.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"Special","trapping":"Drawn or inscribed glyph.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BTDWriPb4tGpCIQm"}
{"name":"Grave Speak","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>It is said the dead know many secrets, and through the black arts a mage can reach beyond death to contact departed souls. Though not evil, many good spellcasters avoid using this power for they feel it disturbs those who have earned their rest.</p>\n<p>In order for this spell to work, it must be directed toward a particular soul. The caster must know the full name of the deceased or possess a personal item, which includes their corpse, or any part of it at least, as well as a treasured item.</p>\n<p>If the spell succeeds, a ghostly voice makes itself known and may be questioned. One question may be asked for each round the spell is active.</p>\n<p>The spirit contacted is not necessarily friendly and can lie, but it may not refuse to answer or make guesses. The Dungeon Master must decide what information the entity knows-the spirit is not omnipotent and typically knows only what it knew in life up to the moment of its death.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, may summon up a demon or other hostile entity. While these spirits cannot usually affect the caster when contacted in this way (they're not summoned), it may try to convince him it is the person he sought, then feed him inaccurate or dangerous information to lead the character to his death.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Runes carved on bodily remains, black candles, \"leather\" books","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4pMWr5ecb28xJlX8"}
{"name":"Jet","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Jet </em>creates a damaging stream that shoots out from the caster. Measure a straight line 1\" wide starting from the character's position. If successful, targets within this area must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} roll versus the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll or suffer 2d10 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.m4eqZIkY7ZpxApvd]{damage}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"2d10","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Lightning bolt, battering ram of pure force, rolling ball of fire.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"U5pM83uJySx4fT5K"}
{"name":"Leaping","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>The target of this spell can @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ERoL9pRXAZWSSFpF]{jump} greater distances than normal. A success doubles his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{jumping} distances, while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} quadruples them. Modifiers are applied after running starts are factored in.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Powerful legs, legs change to an animal's.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hDJ1tm5OZdWm0qgb"}
{"name":"Legerdemain","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Legerdemain </em>allows the character to perform a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action} at range he would normally be capable of doing in person. If the action would require a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.eKNM8zLf1AoL2tmj]{Trait roll}, then the caster rolls the lower of that @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} to both activate the power and determine the results of the action. If the action does not require a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} roll, then his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} is used normally.</p>\n<p>Casting <em>legerdemain </em>is a normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}, but the action performed through the use of it is considered a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{free action} (existing free actions like speaking are unchanged). However the caster is still limited to not duplicating the same action in a round, so it is impossible to cast another spell via <em>legerdemain</em>.</p>\n<p>The power does not create or duplicate the effects of any gear or magical effects upon the caster, but in all other ways, the action is treated exactly as if the caster were performing the action himself at the location. For example, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xCkOFlFmE1WwGXq6]{Fighting} attack does his normal unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage, even if the caster is holding a dagger with <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.D0HgdnbWnDWxFWFf]{smite}</em> on it.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Mimicking action, briefly summoned spirit, astral bi-location.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"F7oZaPhpk6IAzrNa"}
{"name":"Lock/Unlock","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Whether guarding valuables or thwarting pursuers, <em>lock </em>allows the caster to seal a door, treasure chest, or other object with a lock. Attempts to pick or smash the lock suffer a -2 penalty, -4 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the casting roll. Also, the locked object gains +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Toughness}, +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The wizard may open his own locks normally. Opening the <em>lock</em> by any means automatically ends the spell.</p>\n<p><em>Unlock </em>opens any mundane lock, though if the lock is particularly complex, the GM may assign penalties to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. A door sealed with <em>lock </em>gives a -2 or -4 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls to cast this spell.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (+2):&nbsp;</strong>For an additional 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the strength of the spell is increased. The <em>lock </em>is subject to a -4 modifier to break or open the object, and an <em>unlock </em>recieves +2 to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special (lock); Instant (Unlock)","trapping":"Whispered words, scattering dust on a door, aura around lock, tapping a lock three times.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Jq10hOl2CI9NA3id"}
{"name":"Magic Mark","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Magic mark </em>can be visible or invisible. If a <em>magic mark </em>was created as a visible mark, a caster can use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{conceal}</em> <em>(arcana) </em>to temporarily hide it. Casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{detect}</em> <em>(arcana) </em>will reveal a permanent or temporarily concealed <em>magic mark</em>. Casting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.qTiLD4ZYauv51FHi]{dispel} on an <em>magic mark </em>can remove it permanently.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permenant","trapping":"Mystical tattoos, invisible sigils, arcane runes.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EBSdw6OvPr1YZaZ6"}
{"name":"Message","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Message </em>can allow the wizard to deliver a message of up to twenty-five words, or fifty words with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, to a creature in which the wizard is familiar with. The recipient recognizes the sender if it knowns them, and can answer the message in a like manner.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>More Words (+2/+3):</strong> The caster can increase the number of words within the message doubling them from 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} or quadrupling them for 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</li>\n<li><strong>Unknown Recipient (+2):</strong> For 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the caster can send a message to a recipient that he is not familiar with provided the caster knows something that can identify the recipient.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2 miles","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whispered message to an animal, message delivered on the wind.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N6bfaBwVnHsqo3Na"}
{"name":"Mind Rider","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>A character can use this ability to sense through another, including sight, taste, touch, scent, and sound.</p>\n<p>If the subject is willing, the caster simply makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}. If not, the target may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to resist (at -2 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total). If the target succeeds with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the power fails and he knows he was targeted by magic.</p>\n<p>A successful casting allows the character to sense through all his victim's senses. The Range is only limited when the power is activated&mdash;it remains no matter how the target moves afterward.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<h2>Modifiers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+2): </strong>The character can cast this spell on an unseen target up to 50 miles distant if he has an object the subject touched within the last week, or that was precious to him in some way.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Trance, runes on face, face of caster superimposed with that of target.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gljRjiHBZ06lA7O5"}
{"name":"Repair","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Repair </em>allows an artificer to repair damage done to complex machines and objects&mdash;essentially any device that has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bafbq6ovdKFTSCn4]{vehicles} or certain types of constructs and living constructs. This can be any object or machine that has taken damage but are not entirely destroyed.</p>\n<p>Fixing a device or constructs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. A success repairs one Wound and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} repairs two. If the casting fails or does not heal all the damage, the artificer may try again. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the damage can only be repaired through normal hard work and replacement parts.</p>\n<p>For Extras or objects, the DM must first determine if the construct or object is already destroyed. If so, no <em>repair </em>may be attempted. If not, a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll repairs the construct or object.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<h2>Modifiers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Greater Repair (+10):</strong> <em>Greater repairing</em> can actually rebuild objects that are completely broken as long as all parts are still available. This spell may also be used to restore constructs (but not living constructs) that have perished.</li>\n<li><strong>Repair Crippling Injuries (+20): </strong>For Living Constructs, the power can repair a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation} in the Savage Worlds core rules). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it fails, this caster cannot heal that particular injury (but someone else may try). If successful, the subject is Exhausted for 24 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on of hands, working on object with a toolset.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BABaOvPsHwMGAU7k"}
{"name":"Secret Writing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Secret writing</em> requires ten minutes to cast and disguises the contents of a page, scroll, book or other suitable writing material, making it appear however the caster wishes. The caster must specify a command word when the spell is cast. Speaking the command word can reveal the true contents of the page or hide it again. Speaking the command word twice in rapid succession removes the spell completely. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.qTiLD4ZYauv51FHi]{Dispel} removes the effects of the spell and reveals the original contents of the page.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Suggestion (+1): </strong>The caster can designate specific individuals who can read it automatically. To everyone else it appears as described above, but with an added effect of a non-harmful suggestion such as \"This scroll never existed.\" The suggestion must be defined when the power is activated. When the suggestion is triggered, the unauthorized reader must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll originally made to activate the power.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","trapping":"Chanting while writing, enchanted paper, magically transcribed spoken words.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"a1m5CnVJH5JdDjfV"}
{"name":"Sentry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Getting a good night's sleep in the middle of orc country is easier said than done. Sentry duty is tiring and lonely, and a single sentry nodding off can spell disaster. <em>Sentry </em>provides additional security for the wary traveler. It can also be used to safeguard valuables.</p>\n<p>The first version of this spell creates a ghostly sentry who watches over the camp but cannot move further away from the caster than the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 2 in game inches. The sentry has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.ZvwjzMLxsneptV4T]{Notice} of d8, or d10 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, is always alert, and suffers no penalties for bad lighting. Despite being visible as a ghostly form, the <em>sentry </em>is not a physical manifestation and cannot be harmed, though it can be dispelled .</p>\n<p>The <em>sentry </em>may be given instructions on when to sound the alarm but it is not an intelligent, reasoning being. Instructions may contain no more than 10 words and must be clearly defined. For the purposes of identifying potential threats, the sentry has the same knowledge of monsters and hazards as the caster.</p>\n<p>The second variant protects a single object touched by the caster when he invokes the spell. During the casting, the spellcaster may name a number of individuals equal to half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type who can safely touch the object. Anyone else touching it immediately activates the spell, which alerts the caster to the tampering.</p>\n<p>The spell automatically expires at sunset or sunrise, whichever occurs first, and the caster may even sleep while the spell is active. It counts as Maintained.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Special","trapping":"Circle of chalk, powder, or blood, mystic rune, staff thrust into ground.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UJp3fPAz5gJwcPod"}
{"name":"Summon Beast","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Animals have long been associated with wizards, whether it be the familiars of witches or the fetish beasts of shamans. <em>Summon Beast</em> allows a user to summon mundane animals.</p>\n<p>A character may learn this spell while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, but cannot summon any larger creatures until he attains the appropriate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}.</p>\n<p>The beast acts on its creator's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.yJRiqtldrDmMuibA]{Action Card} and follows her basic commands to the best of its ability.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Summon Beast</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1 small animal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>1 medium animal or swarm of rats, birds, insects, or other vermin, or 2 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>1 large, 2 medium or swarms, or 4 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>1 huge, 2 large, 4 medium or swarms, or 6 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Legendary</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>2 huge, 4 large, 6 medium or swarms, or 8 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Small creatures have a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} less than zero. Medium creatures are Size +0 to Size +3. Large covers Size +4 to +7, and Huge is +8 or larger. Swarms share a similar set of statistics and fill a Medium Burst Template.</p>\n<p>The beast is under the total control of the summoner for the Duration of the spell.</p>\n<p>Animals can only be summoned in their natural terrain. So while a wizard may be able to summon a swarm of rats in Sharn, only on the open plains can he call a lion to his side.</p>\n<p>Summoned creatures appear from the nearest appropriate terrain. For instance, rats swarm out of sewers, a lion emerges from jungle or grass on the savannah, and a swarm of birds descends from the clouds or erupts from the trees. If in doubt, assume the beasts \"appear\" 1d10 x 2 yards away from the caster. When the Duration expires, the animal leaves of its own accord.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claw (+1): </strong>The ally can bite or claw at Str+d6.</li>\n<li><strong>Flight (+2): </strong>The ally can fly at Pace 12.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1): </strong>The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Animal bones or feathers of appropriate sort, glyphs, chanting.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hGT6MdrKq6zaTpSK"}
{"name":"Summon Demon","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Most heroes would never seek to consort with the denizens of Khyber or Shavarath. But occasionally, such a feat may be required.</p>\n<p>The cost to summon a demon is equal to its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}&nbsp; die, or twice its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die if it's a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.UPkTmrG7LgZpgshX]{Wild Card} (most powerful demons are).</p>\n<p>If the roll is successful, the demon appears. If the creature was not summoned into a summoning circle or other binding, it likely attacks its caster before it can be given a task. See page 30 for binding the demon through occult means, and the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bind Entity]{bind entity}</em> spell for trapping it with arcane power.</p>\n<p><strong>Tasks: </strong>Once a demon is summoned, and assuming it is bound or otherwise disposed to discussion, the summoner must make a bargain with it. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} test of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirits}. Record the results secretly.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Failure:</em> The demon is uncontrolled and in complete control of its actions. It cannot directly harm the caster but is otherwise free to roam the earth and do as it pleases for 6d6 days. If it happens to roll three 6's on this roll (no more, no less), it remains in the mortal world until slain or banished.</li>\n<li><em>Success:</em> The demon basically follows the instructions it's given but looks for every opportunity to ruin things for the cretin who summoned it. Only if directly chastised or supervised does the demon \"behave.\"</li>\n<li><em>Raise: </em>The demon follows the spirit of the summoner's instructions as well as the letter. It may still cause additional mayhem-it is a demon, after all-but in general it performs as the caster desires.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Casting Time: </strong>The casting time to summon a demon is one minute per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} spent.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialized Demons:</strong> Some demons might only answer specific requests. A demon of vengeance, for example, may only be tasked with exacting vengeance of some sort. This is entirely up to the Game Master, the setting, and the description of the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Communication:</strong> Note that demons are not (generally) telepathic. If the summoner plans on sending the demon out of sight, he'd best give it very specific instructions. Intelligent demons may be given physical equipment (such as cell phones or transmitters in modern settings), but whether or not they actually use these tools is entirely up to them.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Smarts x hours","trapping":"Pentagrams, black candles, animal sacrifices.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0fesmdfOlpDBGOQk"}
{"name":"Summon Elemental","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This powerful spell enables a mage to summon a living spirit of his chosen element&mdash;an \"elemental.\" The creature is completely subject to the whims of the caster.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"5","trapping":"A bit of raw element-a hand full of earth, a flame, water or breath of air.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uAlVMbtHJLUlFDbU"}
{"name":"Teleport","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Teleport </em>allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x5 miles distant, or double that with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a -4 penalty on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don't get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.YneMFEbKXaTaUZGb]{free attack} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.SKOCsEd2ECoe2R92]{Withdrawing from Melee}).</p>\n<p>If casting <em>teleport </em>on a willing subject, the caster decides where they move to, not the target.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><strong>Additional Distance (+3): </strong></strong>The caster may double the distance traveled.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1): </strong>The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Teleport Foe (+2):</strong> Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.7vhAtJWPrNgQ2V0p]{Touch attack}. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}, so the casting must be the second part of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.On57BX9RxFSOBjzj]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12\" away with success and 24\" with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, “phasing” out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZtoRBPJiOlxxXN0y"}
{"name":"Tempest","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Tempest </em>can be used to create or dispel storms. If the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll is successful, an existing storm dissipates or a new one appears overhead with supernatural speed.</p>\n<p>The size of the storm affected is miles in diameter. The power only works outdoors. In areas where storms do not typically exist, such as a desert, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll is made at -4 and may be attempted only once every 24 hours.</p>\n<p>When <em>tempest </em>is cast, the accompanying rain reduces visibility (treat as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.xIvpccPze2BONfJA]{Dark Lighting} conditions), extinguishes most normal fires within 1d10 rounds, and only volatile materials have a random chance of igniting from flame. <em>Tempest </em>conditions inflict a -1 penalty to most actions due to slipping, difficulty hearing, and so on. The Game Master must decide if any actions are unaffected.</p>\n<p>If the mage manages to score a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} when casting <em>tempest</em>, he has created a monstrous storm. Visibility is reduced to just 12\" (and still subject to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.xIvpccPze2BONfJA]{Dark Lighting} ) and the ground turns into a quagmire. Any character running must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} roll or fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.y3j8LVOAXinVVvh7]{prone} and become @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}. Non-game effects include flash floods and lightning strikes, possibly damaging nearby buildings, drowning livestock, and flattening crops.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"15","damage":"","range":"Smarts in miles","duration":"2d4 hours","trapping":"Gestures, words of power.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pZEx5cSnJAuluvdb"}
{"name":"Trinkets","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Trinkets </em>allows a caster to create a minor mundane item weighing less than one pound<em>&mdash;</em>a dagger, a playing card, hand mirror, and so on. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the Duration is in minutes instead of rounds (and is Maintained in minutes as well if desired).</p>\n<p>Conjured items typically appear in a pocket, pouch, or bag to hide the magic that conjures them, but it's not strictly necessary.</p>\n<p>Once the Duration expires, the item fades from reality. If the shyster used conjured coins to buy something, he might be in trouble if the merchant figures out who swindled him.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Complete (+1): </strong>The object is a complete set, though it still must fit under the weight limit. For example, a deck of cards has all 54 cards in it or it is a whole conqueror set, and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Power (+2):</strong> The item can weigh up to two pounds or four with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Slieght of hand, color spray, minor illusions, wave of hand","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aQMnsT2CStogFpc8"}
{"name":"Ward","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><em>Ward </em>creates an invisible barrier that can keep out one specific type of creature determined when the spell is cast. The target creature type must be chosen from the following monstrous abilities: Aquatic, Burrowing, Construct, Demon, Elemental, Ethereal, Flight, Large/Huge, Plant, Poison, Small (affects swarms as well), or Undead.</p>\n<p>The caster first makes his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll and then places a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on himself. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} to the casting roll, the template increases to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}. Creatures of the defined type wishing to enter the Template must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} check against the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total. If they fail, they cannot pass the ward while the spell remains active.</p>\n<p><em>Ward </em>stops the entity from passing through, but only weakens their ability to use other monstrous abilities such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.gHiHPSruN1eag9gT]{Fear} or throwing physical objects. Such abilities or attacks suffer a -2 penalty against beings in the ward, -4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"1 hour","trapping":"Ring or circle of scented oil or holy water or salt, salt, glyphs, leaves, fragrant wood.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KEMrF84NBFiwAfkt"}
{"name":"Whirlwind","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>By making an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, the dragonmarked creates a <em>whirlwind</em>.</p>\n<p>The whirlwind fills a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} placed anywhere within range. Anything coming into contact with it must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll or be knocked prone, at -2 on a raise. The target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} also modifies this roll. Thus, dragons are harder to knock over than halflings.</p>\n<p>The caster can move the whirlwind up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} die in inches each round, but doing so is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.E5UTH6Wqsi9DYlEN]{action}.</p>\n<p>If the center of the whirlwind is moved out of the caster's line of sight, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area Effect (+1): </strong>The effects everything in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Cone Template} or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1): </strong>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll to resist the whirlwind's effects is made at -2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Exhaling, using a fan, spinning motion.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"41Lja48v4lg0xcWI"}
{"name":"Zephyr","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This is the spell casters aligned to the wind are most commonly asked to perform. It gently pushes ships along even in a dead calm, and can also improve top speed in normal winds or during deadly combat.</p>\n<p>It can be used to cancel the spell <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.becalm]{becalm}</em>. In combat, <em>zephyr </em>improves a vessel's current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Handling} by +1 and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} by 25%. It may be cast multiple times, though base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} may never be more than doubled.</p>\n<p>Spellcasters have discovered another use for this spell as well. It is quite adept at dispersing swarms of flying pests, such as wasps. A success @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shakes} the swarm, while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} disperses them (effectively causing a wound). In a few cases, dispersing a swarm actually results in two swarms.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h2>Modifiers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Ships (+3): </strong>For an additional 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} an additional ship can be included in the <em>zephyr </em>wind.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"One ship","duration":"1 hour","trapping":"The hero stands behind the sails, arms out raised and gently blowing, air elemental billows the sails.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_79vmrn8kcd","path":"Powers","color":"#008000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UDkzChexIJopb8j7"}
